Text: This week started off as usual with our client meeting.
Milair was again impressed with the work we've done and the direction that it's heading in, but also again had more ideas of features that needed to be added.
But with limited time left we're just focusing on getting through the list of priorities that Milair provided to us.

She suggested that as well as our final presentation that we give a presentation to the various staff members at the SDHB that will be involved with the software in one way or another, we agreed to this and will probably do it after our own final presentation.
As far as the work completed this week we've made quick progress like I expected to after all of the foundation had been put in place with the database and data binding.

I'm somewhat regretting our decision to use WPF as the MVVM model turned out to be fairly confusing with so many different parts just to make such a minor thing happen, but I'm somewhat suspecting it's possibly because we haven't set it up properly but it's somewhat to be expected jumping straight into WPF MVVM with such a large project instead of getting a fundamental understanding of it through smaller projects.
I can't help but feel like we could have made quicker progress using WinForms instead and just controlling the data manually instead of the automatic updating that binding provides.
We are getting closer to having a viable product at least.
We agreed to cut out holding onto historical changes as it added a rather large complexity to the database and application and just worry about pending changes and then applying them.
The historical data can just be stored through the PDF reports generated.
So I redesigned the database again to make the operations within it much easier.
After that I spent time getting the salary scale functions completed (Adding, updating union and non-union doctors into a pending status to change to the new scale, and editing existing scales).
More recently I've been working on the pending changes and confirmed changes.
On the main page I've pulled the list of pending changes and allowed them to applied individually or in bulk.
